    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-26T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-26T07:00:00-05:00" n="1020"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1020">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">645W.74/10–2652: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1020<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1020fn1">Repeated to London as telegram 346 and unnumbered
                        to Paris, Ankara, the Arab capitals, Rome, Moscow, and Tehran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-10-26T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 26, 1952—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1044. As I set out in <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 1031, Oct 24<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d1020fn2">Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            >Caffery</persName> in telegram 1031, Oct. 24, not printed, informed the
                        Department that the Egyptians now realized that the British had “soundly
                        routed them in Sudan battle and Brit are going ahead with their Sudan
                        arrangements as planned during recent years.” (641.74/10–2452)</note> the
                    Egyptians are fighting hard to save face on the Sudan. <persName
                        corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName> told me at some length last night of his
                    recent convs with various Sudanese dels here. He said even if he is successful
                    he will be bitterly attacked by Wafd, Moslem Bros, Commies and “others too” for
                    having sold the Sudan down the river to the British.</p>
                <p>Egyptians will be forced to accept in essence present Brit program but are
                    working to reach agreed position with all Sudanese factions re amendments to
                    draft constitution and electoral law. Altho number of hurdles remain to be
                    overcome <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName> and his advisors are
                    optimistic that Sudanese will reach agrmt on proposals which <gloss
                        target="#t_GOE1">GOE</gloss> will then support as representing real wishes
                    of Sudanese.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
